11// How small should an innermost loop cluster be before you just
12// entirely unroll the thing. Sized for an architecture with 16 vector
13// registers.
14const int kUnrollLimit = 12;

16// Get the HL_NO_SUBTILING environment variable. Purpose described above.
17bool get_may_subtile() {
18 string no_subtiling_str = get_env_variable("HL_NO_SUBTILING");
19 if (no_subtiling_str == "1") {
20 return false;
21 } else {
22 return true;
23 }
24}
25bool may_subtile() {
26 static bool b = get_may_subtile();
27 return b;
28}

30// Given a multi-dimensional box of dimensionality d, generate a list
31// of candidate tile sizes for it, logarithmically spacing the sizes
32// using the given factor. If 'allow_splits' is false, every dimension
33// must either be one, or the full extent of the box. This function is
34// used to generate candidate tilings when tiling for
35// producer-consumer fusion, or tiling for parallelism.
36vector<vector<int64_t>> generate_tilings(const vector<int64_t> &s, int d, int factor, bool allow_splits) {
37 vector<vector<int64_t>> result;
38 if (d == -1) {
39 result.emplace_back();
40 } else {
41 vector<vector<int64_t>> v = generate_tilings(s, d - 1, factor, allow_splits);
42 // If we're already generated too many tiling configurations
43 // for the inner loops, search the outer loops with coarser
44 // granularity.
45 while (v.size() > (size_t)factor * 100) {
46 factor *= 2;
47 }
48
49 for (auto &t : v) {
50 bool is_full = false, is_const_one = false;
51 // Skip trivial tilings
52 if ((size_t)d == s.size() - 1) {
53 is_const_one = is_full = true;
54 for (int i = 0; i < d; i++) {
55 is_const_one &= (t[i] == 1);
56 is_full &= (t[i] == s[i]);
57 }
58 }
59 t.push_back(0);
60 if (!allow_splits) {
61 if (!is_const_one) {
62 t.back() = 1;
63 result.push_back(t);
64 }
65 if (s[d] != 1 && !is_full) {
66 t.back() = s[d];
67 result.push_back(t);
68 }
69 } else {
70 int max_inner = 0;
71 for (int inner = 1; inner < s[d]; inner *= factor) {
72 int outer = (s[d] + inner - 1) / inner;
73 if (is_const_one && outer == 1) {
74 continue;
75 }
76 if (is_full && outer == s[d]) {
77 continue;
78 }
79 // Stop when we hit inner sizes that would do too much recompute
80 if (inner > 1 && inner * outer * 7 > s[d] * 8) {
81 break;
82 }
83 max_inner = inner;
84 t.back() = outer;
85 result.push_back(t);
86 }
87 for (int outer = 1; outer <= s[d]; outer *= factor) {
88 int inner = (s[d] + outer - 1) / outer;
89 if (is_const_one && outer == 1) {
90 continue;
91 }
92 if (is_full && outer == s[d]) {
93 continue;
94 }
95 // Stop when we get into the regime covered by the loop above.
96 if (outer > 1 && inner < max_inner * 2) {
97 break;
98 }
99 // Or when the wasted compute gets too bad.
100 if (inner * outer * 7 > s[d] * 8) {
101 break;
102 }
103 t.back() = outer;
104 result.push_back(t);
105 }
106
107 // The sequence above (in terms of the inner loop)
108 // goes 1 2 4 8 16 ... but 3 is an important inner
109 // tiling factor for matrix multiply/gemm-type loops
110 // which try to use 12 vector registers.
111 int inner3 = 3;
112 int outer3 = (s[d] + inner3 - 1) / inner3;
113 if (factor == 2 && inner3 < s[d] && outer3 < s[d] && outer3 > 1) {
114 if (inner3 * outer3 * 7 <= s[d] * 8) {
115 t.back() = outer3;
116 result.push_back(t);
117 }
118 }
119 }
120 }
121 }
122 return result;
123}

125void LoopNest::copy_from(const LoopNest &n) {
126 size = n.size;

140// Hash the loop structure and sizes up to a fixed depth. This is
141// used as the hash function for the coarse-to-fine beam search in
142// the paper.
143void LoopNest::structural_hash(uint64_t &h, int depth) const {
144 if (depth < 0) {
145 return;
146 }
147
148 // Which Funcs are store_at this level?
149 for (const auto *n : store_at) {
150 hash_combine(h, n->id);
151 }
152
153 hash_combine(h, -1);
154
155 // Which Funcs are compute_at this level?
156 for (const auto &c : children) {
157 hash_combine(h, c->stage->id);
158 }
159
160 // Add a barrier to ensure that moving something from the last
161 // compute_at to the first inlined doesn't result in the same
162 // hash.
163 hash_combine(h, -1);
164
165 // Which Funcs are inlined at this level?
166 for (auto it = inlined.begin(); it != inlined.end(); it++) {
167 hash_combine(h, it.key()->id);
168 }
169
170 hash_combine(h, -1);
171
172 if (depth > 0) {
173 // What are the loop sizes of the children?
174 for (const auto &c : children) {
175 for (int64_t s : c->size) {
176 if (depth == 1) {
177 // Just take the most significant bit: is it one or not?
178 s = (s > 1) ? 1 : 0;
179 }
180 hash_combine(h, s);
181 }
182 }
183
184 // Which dimension are we vectorized over?
185 hash_combine(h, vectorized_loop_index);
186 }
187
188 if (depth > 1) {
189 // Descend into children
190 for (const auto &c : children) {
191 c->structural_hash(h, depth - 2);
192 }
193 }
194}

196// Compute all the sites of interest for each pipeline stage
197void LoopNest::get_sites(StageMap<Sites> &sites,
198 const LoopNest *task,
199 const LoopNest *parent) const {
200 if (!task && !is_root()) {
201 task = this;
202 }
203 for (const auto &c : children) {
204 c->get_sites(sites, task, this);
205 }
206 if (parent && node != parent->node) {
207 auto &s = sites.get_or_create(stage);
208 s.compute = parent;
209 s.produce = this;
210 s.task = task;
211 }
212 for (const auto *f : store_at) {
213 for (const auto &s : f->stages) {
214 sites.get_or_create(&s).store = this;
215 }
216 }
217 for (auto it = inlined.begin(); it != inlined.end(); it++) {
218 auto &s = sites.get_or_create(&(it.key()->stages[0]));
219 s.inlined = true;
220 s.compute = s.store = s.produce = s.innermost = this;
221 s.task = task;
222 }
223 if (innermost) {
224 sites.get_or_create(stage).innermost = this;
225 }
226}

228// Do a recursive walk over the loop nest computing features to feed the cost model.
229void LoopNest::compute_features(const FunctionDAG &dag,
230 const MachineParams &params,
231 const StageMap<Sites> &sites,
232 int64_t instances,
233 int64_t parallelism,
234 const LoopNest *parent,
235 const LoopNest *grandparent,
236 const LoopNest &root,
237 int64_t *working_set,
238 StageMap<ScheduleFeatures> *features,
239 bool use_cached_features) const {
240 int64_t working_set_here = 0;
241
242 int64_t loop_instances = 1, parallel_tasks = 1;
243 bool in_impure = false;
244 for (int idx = (int)size.size() - 1; idx >= 0; idx--) {
245 size_t i = size[idx];
246 loop_instances *= i;
247 if (stage->loop[idx].pure && !in_impure) {
248 if (params.parallelism > 1 &&
249 (parallel || (parent->is_root() && parallel_tasks < params.parallelism))) {
250 // Either we've picked our parallel tiling, or
251 // it's not yet determined. Assume we'll not split
252 // any loops and just stop after we hit the
253 // required number of cores
254 parallel_tasks *= i;
255 // If we haven't picked out parallel tiling yet,
256 // assume that we'll target 8*cores when we do,
257 // which is a common rule of thumb.
258 if (!parallel && parallel_tasks > params.parallelism * 8) {
259 // We would split this loop
260 parallel_tasks = params.parallelism * 8;
261 }
262 }
263 } else if (i != 1) {
264 in_impure = true;
265 }
266 }
267
268 int64_t subinstances = instances * loop_instances;
269
270 for (const auto *node : store_at) {
271 // Figure out the features at the store_at level
272 const auto &bounds = get_bounds(node);
273
274 for (size_t s = 0; s < node->stages.size(); s++) {
275 // TODO: Lift invariants from this loop. Most of it's the same for every stage.
276 internal_assert(!node->is_input);
277 ScheduleFeatures &feat = features->get_or_create(&(node->stages[s]));
278
279 feat.num_realizations = subinstances;
280
281 feat.points_computed_per_realization = 1;
282 feat.num_scalars = feat.num_vectors = subinstances;
283 bool vectorized = false;
284 for (int i = 0; i < (int)node->stages[s].loop.size(); i++) {
285 const auto &p = bounds->loops(s, i);
286 int64_t extent = p.extent();
287 feat.points_computed_per_realization *= extent;
288 if (i == sites.get(&(node->stages[s])).produce->vectorized_loop_index) {
289 // Assumes that we're not going to split
290 // things such that non-native-width
291 // vectorization is a problem, except for the
292 // tail.
293 feat.num_vectors *= extent / node->stages[s].vector_size;
294 feat.num_scalars *= extent % node->stages[s].vector_size;
295 vectorized = true;
296 } else {
297 feat.num_vectors *= extent;
298 feat.num_scalars *= extent;
299 }
300 }
301 if (!vectorized) {
302 feat.num_vectors = 0;
303 }
304 feat.points_computed_total = feat.points_computed_per_realization * feat.num_realizations;
305
306 feat.bytes_at_realization = node->bytes_per_point;
307 for (int i = 0; i < node->dimensions; i++) {
308 const auto &p = bounds->region_computed(i);
309 feat.bytes_at_realization *= p.extent();
310 }
311 int64_t innermost_storage_extent = 1;
312 int v = sites.get(&(node->stages[s])).produce->vector_dim;
313 if (v >= 0 && node->dimensions > 0) {
314 innermost_storage_extent = bounds->region_computed(v).extent();
315 }
316 feat.innermost_bytes_at_realization = node->bytes_per_point * innermost_storage_extent;
317
318 if (!is_root()) {
319 feat.bytes_at_task = feat.bytes_at_realization;
320 feat.innermost_bytes_at_task = feat.innermost_bytes_at_realization;
321 }
322 }
323 }
324
325 if (is_root()) {
326 // TODO: This block of code is repeated below. Refactor
327 for (const auto &c : children) {
328
329 const uint64_t hash_of_producers = sites.get(c->stage).hash_of_producers_stored_at_root;
330
331 if (use_cached_features) {
332 // Checks if the features cache has seen this state before, and use the cached features if so.
333 if (c->features_cache.count(hash_of_producers) > 0) {
334 const auto &entry = c->features_cache.at(hash_of_producers);
335
336 for (auto it = entry.begin(); it != entry.end(); it++) {
337 const auto *stage_ptr = it.key();
338 const auto &feat = it.value();
339
340 features->insert(stage_ptr, feat);
341 }
342
343 // 'working_set_here' is required below for computing the
344 // root-level features so we compute the value that it
345 // would have had if the current loop nest had not been
346 // memoized
347 int64_t working_set_c{0};
348 c->compute_working_set_from_features(&working_set_c, features);
349 working_set_here += working_set_c;
350 continue; // no need to recompute fetures
351 }
352 }
353
354 c->compute_features(dag, params, sites, subinstances, parallelism, this, parent, root, &working_set_here, features, use_cached_features);
355
356 if (use_cached_features) {
357 // Cache these features for future reference.
358 c->features_cache[hash_of_producers].make_large(dag.nodes[0].stages[0].max_id);
359 c->memoize_features(c->features_cache[hash_of_producers], features);
360 }
361 }
362
363 for (const auto *node : store_at) {
364 auto &feat = features->get(&(node->stages[0]));
365 working_set_here += feat.bytes_at_production;
366 }
367 for (const auto *node : store_at) {
368 for (const auto &s : node->stages) {
369 auto &feat = features->get(&s);
370 feat.working_set_at_realization = working_set_here;
371 }
372 }
373 for (const auto &c : children) {
374 if (c->node != node) {
375 auto &feat = features->get(c->stage);
376 feat.working_set_at_production = working_set_here;
377 }
378 }
379
380 // Figure out the root-level features for every Func
381 for (auto it = features->begin(); it != features->end(); it++) {
382 const auto *stage = it.key();
383 const auto *node = stage->node;
384 auto &feat = it.value();
385 const auto &root_bounds = root.get_bounds(node);
386
387 feat.bytes_at_root = node->bytes_per_point;
388 for (int i = 0; i < node->dimensions; i++) {
389 const auto &p = root_bounds->region_computed(i);
390 feat.bytes_at_root *= p.extent();
391 }
392
393 feat.working_set_at_root = working_set_here;
394
395 const auto *p = sites.get(stage).produce;
396 if (p) {
397 // Extent of the innermost dimension in the storage layout
398 int64_t innermost_storage_extent = 1;
399 int v = p->vector_dim;
400 if (v >= 0 && v < node->dimensions) {
401 innermost_storage_extent = root_bounds->region_computed(v).extent();
402 }
403 feat.innermost_bytes_at_root = node->bytes_per_point * innermost_storage_extent;
404 } else {
405 feat.innermost_bytes_at_root = 0;
406 }
407
408 feat.points_computed_minimum = 1;
409 for (int i = 0; i < (int)stage->loop.size(); i++) {
410 const auto &p = root_bounds->loops(stage->index, i);
411 feat.points_computed_minimum *= p.extent();
412 }
413
414 if (node->stages.size() == 1 && !node->is_output) {
415 int64_t points_computed_minimum_if_inlined = 0;
416 for (auto *e : node->outgoing_edges) {
417 points_computed_minimum_if_inlined += features->get(e->consumer).points_computed_minimum * e->calls;
418 }
419 feat.points_computed_minimum = std::min(feat.points_computed_minimum, (double)points_computed_minimum_if_inlined);
420 }
421
422 // When memoizing, we need to recompute features for inlined Funcs
423 // so we reset them here
424 if (use_cached_features && sites.get(stage).inlined) {
425 feat.inlined_calls = 0;
426 feat.num_scalars = 0;
427 feat.innermost_pure_loop_extent = 0;
428 feat.outer_parallelism = 0;
429 }
430 }
431
432 if (use_cached_features) {
433 for (const auto &c : children) {
434 uint64_t hash_of_producers = sites.get(c->stage).hash_of_producers_stored_at_root;
435
436 // When computing feat.points_computed_minimum above, the order
437 // of nodes considered is possibly different from the loop nest
438 // traversal order so 'features->get(e->consumer).points_computed_minimum'
439 // may not have been computed when it is accessed as a memoized
440 // feature. We memoize 'points_computed_minimum' here to ensure
441 // its value is always available
442 if (c->features_cache.count(hash_of_producers) > 0) {
443 c->memoize_points_computed_minimum(c->features_cache[hash_of_producers], features);
444 }
445 }
446 recompute_inlined_features(sites, features);
447 }
448
449 return;
450 }
451
452 int64_t subparallelism = parallel_tasks * parallelism;
453
454 // Figure out the features at the compute_at level
455 internal_assert(!stage->node->is_input);
456 ScheduleFeatures &feat = features->get_or_create(stage);
457
458 if (innermost) {
459 if (vectorized_loop_index >= 0 && vectorized_loop_index < (int)size.size()) {
460 feat.vector_size = size[vectorized_loop_index];
461 } else {
462 feat.vector_size = 1;
463 }
464 if (feat.vector_size == 1) {
465 // They're all scalars
466 feat.num_scalars += feat.num_vectors;
467 feat.num_vectors = 0;
468 }
469 } else {
470 // We want these features just outside the innermost loop,
471 // so just set them at every level and let them get
472 // progressively overwritten as we descend the loop nest
473 // tree.
474 size_t idx = 0;
475 feat.innermost_loop_extent = 1;
476 feat.innermost_pure_loop_extent = 1;
477 for (const auto &l : stage->loop) {
478 feat.innermost_loop_extent *= size[idx];
479 if (!l.rvar) {
480 feat.innermost_pure_loop_extent *= size[idx];
481 }
482 idx++;
483 }
484 }
485
486 const bool at_task = parent->is_root();
487 const bool at_production = parent->node != node;
488 const bool at_pure_production = at_production && stage->index == 0;
489
490 if (at_task) {
491 if (parallel) {
492 const auto &bounds = get_bounds(node);
493 feat.bytes_at_task = node->bytes_per_point;
494 int64_t innermost_storage_extent = 1;
495 for (int i = 0; i < node->dimensions; i++) {
496 int64_t outer = 1;
497 for (size_t l = 0; l < stage->loop.size(); l++) {
498 if (stage->loop[l].var == node->func.args()[i]) {
499 outer = size[l];
500 break;
501 }
502 }
503 const auto &p = bounds->region_computed(i);
504 int64_t extent = p.extent();
505 extent /= outer;
506 feat.bytes_at_task *= extent;
507 if (i == vector_dim) {
508 innermost_storage_extent = extent;
509 }
510 }
511 feat.innermost_bytes_at_task = node->bytes_per_point * innermost_storage_extent;
512 } else {
513 // How this loop will be parallelized is not yet
514 // determined. Use optimistic values for the features.
515 feat.bytes_at_task = (feat.bytes_at_realization + params.parallelism - 1) / params.parallelism;
516 feat.innermost_bytes_at_task = std::min(feat.bytes_at_task, feat.innermost_bytes_at_realization);
517 }
518
519 feat.unique_bytes_read_per_task = 0;
520 feat.unique_lines_read_per_task = 0;
521
522 // We're at a parallel for loop. Check all the accesses
523 // done by Funcs inside this loop to values computed
524 // outside of it to figure out how much data we'll be
525 // streaming onto the core.
526 vector<const FunctionDAG::Edge *> pending;
527 set<const FunctionDAG::Node *> done;
528 for (const auto *e : stage->incoming_edges) {
529 pending.push_back(e);
530 }
531 while (!pending.empty()) {
532 const auto *e = pending.back();
533 pending.pop_back();
534 if (done.count(e->producer)) {
535 continue;
536 }
537 done.insert(e->producer);
538 const auto &site = sites.get(&(e->producer->stages[0]));
539 if (site.store->is_root()) {
540 const auto &b = get_bounds(e->producer);
541 int64_t bytes = e->producer->bytes_per_point, lines = 1;
542 int64_t max_extent = 1;
543 // clang-format off
544 int vector_dim = (e->producer->is_input ? 0 :
545 site.produce != nullptr ? site.produce->vector_dim :
546 -1);
547 // clang-format on
548 for (int i = 0; i < e->producer->dimensions; i++) {
549 int64_t extent = b->region_required(i).extent();
550 max_extent = std::max(extent, max_extent);
551 bytes *= extent;
552 if (i != vector_dim) {
553 lines *= extent;
554 }
555 }
556 if (!e->producer->is_input && site.produce == nullptr) {
557 // We haven't scheduled the producer so we
558 // don't know the memory layout yet. Assume
559 // the best case.
560 lines /= max_extent;
561 }
562 feat.unique_bytes_read_per_task += bytes;
563 feat.unique_lines_read_per_task += lines;
564
565 } else if (site.produce != nullptr) {
566 // Computation must be nested inside this task or inlined into it.
567 for (const auto &s : e->producer->stages) {
568 for (const auto *e2 : s.incoming_edges) {
569 pending.push_back(e2);
570 }
571 }
572 }
573 }
574 }
575
576 if (at_production) {
577 feat.num_productions = instances;
578 feat.inner_parallelism = parallel_tasks;
579 feat.outer_parallelism = parallelism;
580 feat.native_vector_size = stage->vector_size;
581
582 const auto &bounds = parent->get_bounds(node);
583
584 feat.bytes_at_production = node->bytes_per_point;
585 for (int i = 0; i < node->dimensions; i++) {
586 const auto &p = bounds->region_computed(i);
587 feat.bytes_at_production *= p.extent();
588 }
589 int64_t innermost_storage_extent = 1;
590 if (vector_dim >= 0 && node->dimensions > 0) {
591 innermost_storage_extent = bounds->region_computed(vector_dim).extent();
592 }
593 feat.innermost_bytes_at_production = node->bytes_per_point * innermost_storage_extent;
594 }
595
596 // Recurse inwards
597 for (const auto &c : children) {
598 c->compute_features(dag, params, sites, subinstances, subparallelism, this, parent, root, &working_set_here, features, use_cached_features);
599 }
600 for (const auto *node : store_at) {
601 auto &feat = features->get(&(node->stages[0]));
602 working_set_here += feat.bytes_at_production;
603 }
604 for (const auto *node : store_at) {
605 for (const auto &s : node->stages) {
606 auto &feat = features->get(&s);
607 feat.working_set_at_realization = working_set_here;
608 }
609 }
610 for (const auto &c : children) {
611 if (c->node != node) {
612 auto &feat = features->get(c->stage);
613 feat.working_set_at_production = working_set_here;
614 }
615 }
616
617 if (at_task) {
618 set_working_set_at_task_feature(working_set_here, features);
619 }
620
621 if (at_production) {
622 feat.working_set = working_set_here;
623 }
624
625 if (innermost) {
626 bool parent_unrolled =
627 (feat.innermost_pure_loop_extent <= kUnrollLimit &&
628 parent->node == node);
629
630 if (parent_unrolled) {
631 const auto &grandparent_bounds = grandparent->get_bounds(node);
632 for (size_t i = 0; i < parent->size.size(); i++) {
633 if (!stage->loop[i].rvar) {
634 const auto &l = grandparent_bounds->loops(parent->stage->index, i);
635 parent_unrolled &= l.constant_extent();
636 }
637 }
638 }
639
640 if (parent_unrolled) {
641 feat.unrolled_loop_extent = feat.innermost_pure_loop_extent;
642 } else {
643 feat.unrolled_loop_extent = 1;
644 }
645 }
646
647 *working_set += working_set_here;
648
649 // Analyze all memory dependencies of this stage, looking
650 // through any Funcs inlined into it. This is where we track
651 // things like vector gathers.
652 int64_t bytes_loaded = 0, lines_loaded = 0, allocation_bytes_loaded = 0;
653 double num_dense_loads = 0, num_broadcasts = 0,
654 num_gathers = 0, num_stride_2_loads = 0,
655 num_stride_3_loads = 0, num_stride_4_loads = 0,
656 num_loads = 0;
657 if (innermost || at_production) { // These are the sites at which we compute load footprints
658 // Pick the site at which we will compute the footprint relationship
659 const auto &consumer_site = sites.get(stage);
660
661 // The store_at location of the consumer
662 const auto *consumer_store_site = innermost ? parent : consumer_site.store;
663
664 // The parallel loop of the consumer
665 const auto *consumer_task_site = consumer_site.task;
666
667 int64_t consumer_instances = innermost ? instances : feat.num_realizations;
668 internal_assert(consumer_instances != 0);
669
670 vector<const FunctionDAG::Node::Stage *> pending;
671 pending.emplace_back(stage);
672 vector<pair<LoadJacobian, FunctionDAG::Node *>> jacobians;
673 set<const FunctionDAG::Node *> done;
674 while (!pending.empty()) {
675 const auto *p = pending.back();
676 pending.pop_back();
677 const auto &next_edges = p->incoming_edges;
678 for (const auto *e : next_edges) {
679 internal_assert(sites.contains(&(e->producer->stages[0])))
680 << "No site found for " << e->producer->func.name() << "\n";
681
682 const auto &site = sites.get(&(e->producer->stages[0]));
683
684 bool producer_has_been_scheduled = e->producer->is_input || (site.produce != nullptr);
685
686 if (innermost) {
687 if (e->consumer == stage) {
688 for (const auto &j : e->load_jacobians) {
689 jacobians.emplace_back(j, e->producer);
690 }
691 } else {
692 // Consumer was inlined. Multiply the Jacobians to look through it.
693 decltype(jacobians) new_jacobians;
694 for (auto &j1 : jacobians) {
695 if (e->consumer->node == j1.second) {
696 for (const auto &j2 : e->load_jacobians) {
697 LoadJacobian j = j2 * j1.first;
698 new_jacobians.emplace_back(j, e->producer);
699 }
700 } else {
701 new_jacobians.emplace_back(std::move(j1));
702 }
703 }
704 jacobians.swap(new_jacobians);
705 }
706 }
707
708 if (site.inlined) {
709 // Recursively examine the inputs
710 pending.emplace_back(&(e->producer->stages[0]));
711 continue;
712 }
713
714 // The producer's compute_at site
715 const auto *producer_compute_site = site.compute;
716
717 // The producer's store_at site
718 const auto *producer_store_site = site.store;
719
720 // The region required of the producer at various sites.
721 const auto &bounds = consumer_store_site->get_bounds(e->producer);
722 const auto &task_bounds = consumer_task_site->get_bounds(e->producer);
723 const auto &producer_compute_bounds = producer_compute_site->get_bounds(e->producer);
724 const auto &producer_store_bounds = producer_store_site->get_bounds(e->producer);
725
726 // Compute memory footprints in terms of the
727 // number of contiguous lines, and the number of
728 // bytes.
729 int64_t footprint = e->producer->bytes_per_point;
730 int64_t compute_footprint = footprint;
731 int64_t store_footprint = footprint;
732 int64_t task_footprint = footprint;
733 int64_t line_footprint = 1;
734 int64_t compute_line_footprint = 1;
735 int64_t store_line_footprint = 1;
736 int64_t task_line_footprint = 1;
737
738 if (e->producer->is_input) {
739 // This node represents an input. Its sites
740 // should be at the root level.
741 internal_assert(producer_store_site->is_root());
742 internal_assert(producer_compute_site->is_root());
743 }
744
745 if (innermost) {
746
747 // Grab the Jacobians that describe the memory dependence
748 for (const auto &jac : jacobians) {
749 if (jac.second != e->producer) {
750 continue;
751 }
752 double n = jac.first.count();
753
754 // Classify them to figure out what's going on in the vector dimension.
755 bool vector_broadcast = true;
756 bool dense_vector_load = true;
757 bool stride_2_vector_load = true;
758 bool stride_3_vector_load = true;
759 bool stride_4_vector_load = true;
760 int producer_innermost_dim =
761 (e->producer->is_input ? 0 : // Assume default storage layout for inputs
762 !producer_has_been_scheduled ? -1 :
763 site.produce->vector_dim);
764 if (vectorized_loop_index >= 0) {
765 if (!producer_has_been_scheduled) {
766 // Operate optimistically and just
767 // see if *any* dimension of the
768 // producer would make for a good
769 // load.
770 int count[5] = {0, 0, 0, 0, 0};
771 for (int i = 0; i < e->producer->dimensions; i++) {
772 auto stride = jac.first(i, vectorized_loop_index);
773 // stride is a rational. Check to see if it's a small integer.
774 if (stride == 0) {
775 count[0]++;
776 } else if (stride == 1) {
777 count[1]++;
778 } else if (stride == 2) {
779 count[2]++;
780 } else if (stride == 3) {
781 count[3]++;
782 } else if (stride == 4) {
783 count[4]++;
784 }
785 }
786 vector_broadcast = (count[0] == e->producer->dimensions);
787 dense_vector_load = (count[0] == e->producer->dimensions - 1 && count[1] == 1);
788 stride_2_vector_load = (count[0] == e->producer->dimensions - 1 && count[2] == 1);
789 stride_3_vector_load = (count[0] == e->producer->dimensions - 1 && count[3] == 1);
790 stride_4_vector_load = (count[0] == e->producer->dimensions - 1 && count[4] == 1);
791 } else {
792 for (int i = 0; i < e->producer->dimensions; i++) {
793 auto stride = jac.first(i, vectorized_loop_index);
794 vector_broadcast &= stride == 0;
795 if (i == producer_innermost_dim) {
796 dense_vector_load &= stride == 1;
797 stride_2_vector_load &= stride == 2;
798 stride_3_vector_load &= stride == 3;
799 stride_4_vector_load &= stride == 4;
800 } else {
801 dense_vector_load &= stride == 0;
802 stride_2_vector_load &= stride == 0;
803 stride_3_vector_load &= stride == 0;
804 stride_4_vector_load &= stride == 0;
805 // TODO: Check for strided
806 // loads across non-innermost
807 // dims, and use to count the
808 // number of pages, cache
809 // lines, cache conflict misses, etc.
810 }
811 }
812 }
813 }
814
815 // Is this load loop-invariant over an
816 // unrolled block? If so, we amortize the
817 // number of loads to account for
818 // LICM. This is the key performance
819 // optimization you get from unrolling the
820 // inner loop of a gemm or conv, so it's
821 // important to capture it in the
822 // featurization.
823 int64_t amortization = 1;
824 if (feat.unrolled_loop_extent > 1) {
825 for (size_t idx = 0; idx < stage->loop.size(); idx++) {
826 if (!stage->loop[idx].rvar) {
827 bool loop_invariant = true;
828 for (int i = 0; i < e->producer->dimensions; i++) {
829 if (!(jac.first(i, idx) == 0)) {
830 loop_invariant = false;
831 break;
832 }
833 }
834 if (loop_invariant) {
835 amortization *= parent->size[idx];
836 }
837 }
838 }
839 }
840 n /= amortization;
841
842 num_loads += n;
843 if (vector_broadcast) {
844 num_broadcasts += n;
845 } else if (dense_vector_load) {
846 num_dense_loads += n;
847 } else if (stride_2_vector_load) {
848 num_stride_2_loads += n;
849 } else if (stride_3_vector_load) {
850 num_stride_3_loads += n;
851 } else if (stride_4_vector_load) {
852 num_stride_4_loads += n;
853 } else {
854 num_gathers += n;
855 }
856 }
857 }
858
859 // Already dealt with the footprints for this producer via some other path
860 if (done.find(e->producer) != done.end()) {
861 continue;
862 }
863
864 done.insert(e->producer);
865
866 // Now look at the shapes of the regions read from
867 // the producer at various sites.
868 int64_t max_extent = 1, max_compute_extent = 1, max_store_extent = 1, max_task_extent = 1;
869 for (int i = 0; i < e->producer->dimensions; i++) {
870 auto p = bounds->region_required(i);
871 auto compute_p = producer_compute_bounds->region_computed(i);
872 auto store_p = producer_store_bounds->region_required(i);
873 auto task_p = task_bounds->region_required(i);
874
875 // Check some invariants
876 internal_assert(store_p.min() <= store_p.max()) << store_p.min() << " " << store_p.max() << "\n";
877 internal_assert(compute_p.min() <= compute_p.max()) << compute_p.min() << " " << compute_p.max() << "\n";
878 internal_assert(task_p.min() <= task_p.max()) << task_p.min() << " " << task_p.max() << "\n";
879
880 int64_t extent = p.extent();
881 int64_t compute_extent = compute_p.extent();
882 int64_t store_extent = store_p.extent();
883 int64_t task_extent = task_p.extent();
884
885 max_extent = std::max(extent, max_extent);
886 max_compute_extent = std::max(compute_extent, max_compute_extent);
887 max_store_extent = std::max(store_extent, max_store_extent);
888 max_task_extent = std::max(task_extent, max_task_extent);
889
890 footprint *= extent;
891 compute_footprint *= compute_extent;
892 store_footprint *= store_extent;
893 task_footprint *= task_extent;
894
895 bool dense = ((e->producer->is_input && i == 0) ||
896 (site.produce != nullptr && i == site.produce->vector_dim));
897 if (!dense) {
898 line_footprint *= extent;
899 compute_line_footprint *= compute_extent;
900 store_line_footprint *= store_extent;
901 task_line_footprint *= task_extent;
902 }
903 }
904
905 if (!producer_has_been_scheduled) {
906 // Optimistically assume it gets vectorized
907 // along whatever dimension makes these
908 // numbers the smallest.
909 line_footprint /= max_extent;
910 compute_line_footprint /= max_compute_extent;
911 store_line_footprint /= max_store_extent;
912 task_line_footprint /= max_task_extent;
913 }
914
915 int64_t store_instances_per_consumption = 1;
916
917 if (producer_has_been_scheduled && !e->producer->is_input) {
918 const auto &producer_feat = features->get_or_create(&(e->producer->stages[0]));
919
920 if (producer_feat.num_realizations) {
921 // The producer's realization is nested inside this Func's realization
922 const int64_t producer_store_instances = producer_feat.num_realizations;
923 if (producer_store_instances > consumer_instances) {
924 store_instances_per_consumption = producer_store_instances / consumer_instances;
925 }
926 }
927 }
928
929 allocation_bytes_loaded += compute_footprint;
930
931 if (store_instances_per_consumption > 1) {
932 // The producer is nested inside the consumer
933 bytes_loaded += store_footprint;
934 // Due to folding, the actual buffer size is smaller than the bounds at the store level
935 lines_loaded += store_line_footprint;
936 } else {
937 // The consumer is consuming some portion of a larger producer computed earlier
938 bytes_loaded += footprint;
939 lines_loaded += line_footprint;
940 }
941
942 // We compute (but never use) these; computing them is cheap,
943 // so let's leave in for future reference, but mark as 'ignore me'
944 // to avoid clang-tidy warnings.
945 (void)compute_line_footprint;
946 (void)task_line_footprint;
947 }
948 }
949 }
950
951 if (at_production) {
952 // Properties of the realization, but the values are
953 // computable at the production site because that's where
954 // the consumers are.
955 internal_assert(bytes_loaded >= 0) << "Negative bytes loaded: " << bytes_loaded << "\n";
956 feat.allocation_bytes_read_per_realization = allocation_bytes_loaded;
957 feat.unique_bytes_read_per_realization = bytes_loaded;
958 feat.unique_lines_read_per_realization = lines_loaded;
959
960 if (!at_pure_production) {
961 // Also pessimistically assume this update definition relies on the entirety of the produced region so far.
962 // TODO: This overbills scatters, or writes to a sub-window.
963 internal_assert(bytes_loaded >= 0) << "Negative bytes at production: " << feat.bytes_at_production << "\n";
964 feat.unique_bytes_read_per_realization += feat.bytes_at_production;
965 feat.unique_lines_read_per_realization += feat.bytes_at_production / feat.innermost_bytes_at_production;
966 feat.allocation_bytes_read_per_realization += feat.bytes_at_production;
967 }
968 }
969
970 if (innermost) {
971 feat.points_computed_per_production = subinstances / feat.num_productions;
972 // Halide codegens strided loads for small strides as a
973 // large dense vector load and a cheap swizzle. ARM even
974 // has instructions that do this for free on load
975 // (e.g. vld4).
976 feat.vector_loads_per_vector = (num_dense_loads +
977 2 * num_stride_2_loads +
978 3 * num_stride_3_loads +
979 4 * num_stride_4_loads);
980 feat.scalar_loads_per_vector = num_broadcasts + feat.vector_size * num_gathers;
981 feat.scalar_loads_per_scalar = num_loads;
982 if (stage->index > 0) {
983 // Assume at update definitions we do a self-load
984 feat.vector_loads_per_vector++;
985 feat.scalar_loads_per_scalar++;
986 }
987 feat.unique_bytes_read_per_vector = bytes_loaded;
988 feat.unique_lines_read_per_vector = lines_loaded;
989 }
990
991 // Track features for inlined Funcs
992 for (auto it = inlined.begin(); it != inlined.end(); it++) {
993 const auto *f = it.key();
994 internal_assert(f);
995 auto &inlined_feat = features->get_or_create(&(f->stages[0]));
996 inlined_feat.inlined_calls += it.value() * subinstances;
997 inlined_feat.num_vectors += it.value() * feat.num_vectors;
998 inlined_feat.num_scalars += it.value() * feat.num_scalars;
999 inlined_feat.native_vector_size = stage->vector_size;
1000 if (inlined_feat.vector_size > 0) {
1001 inlined_feat.vector_size = std::min(inlined_feat.vector_size, (double)stage->vector_size);
1002 } else {
1003 inlined_feat.vector_size = feat.vector_size;
1004 }
1005 if (inlined_feat.innermost_pure_loop_extent > 0) {
1006 inlined_feat.innermost_pure_loop_extent =
1007 std::min(inlined_feat.innermost_pure_loop_extent,
1008 feat.innermost_pure_loop_extent);
1009 } else {
1010 inlined_feat.innermost_pure_loop_extent = feat.innermost_pure_loop_extent;
1011 }
1012 inlined_feat.inner_parallelism = 1;
1013 inlined_feat.outer_parallelism = parallelism;
1014
1015 // Memoize intermediate features, based on stage.
1016 if (use_cached_features) {
1017 const auto &block = sites.get(stage).task;
1018 uint64_t hash_of_producers = sites.get(block->stage).hash_of_producers_stored_at_root;
1019 auto &intermediate_map = block->feature_intermediates_cache[hash_of_producers].get_or_create(&(f->stages[0]));
1020 auto &intermediate = intermediate_map.get_or_create(stage);
1021
1022 intermediate.inlined_calls = it.value() * subinstances;
1023 intermediate.num_scalars = it.value() * feat.num_scalars;
1024 intermediate.innermost_pure_loop_extent = feat.innermost_pure_loop_extent;
1025 intermediate.outer_parallelism = parallelism;
1026 }
1027 }
1028}
1029
1030// Get the region required of a Func at this site, from which we
1031// know what region would be computed if it were scheduled here,
1032// and what its loop nest would be.
1033const Bound &LoopNest::get_bounds(const FunctionDAG::Node *f) const {
1034 if (bounds.contains(f)) {
1035 const Bound &b = bounds.get(f);
1036 // Expensive validation for debugging
1037 // b->validate();
1038 return b;
1039 }
1040 auto *bound = f->make_bound();
1041
1042 // Compute the region required
1043 if (f->is_output && is_root()) {
1044 internal_assert(f->outgoing_edges.empty()) << "Outputs that access other outputs not yet supported\n";
1045 // It's an output. Use the bounds estimate.
1046 for (int i = 0; i < f->dimensions; i++) {
1047 bound->region_required(i) = f->estimated_region_required[i];
1048 }
1049 } else {
1050 internal_assert(!f->outgoing_edges.empty())
1051 << "No consumers of " << f->func.name()
1052 << " at loop over " << (is_root() ? "root" : node->func.name()) << "\n";
1053 auto init = Span::empty_span();
1054 for (int i = 0; i < f->dimensions; i++) {
1055 bound->region_required(i) = init;
1056 }
1057
1058 for (const auto *e : f->outgoing_edges) {
1059 // Ignore consumers outside of this loop nest
1060 if (!is_root() &&
1061 (stage != e->consumer) &&
1062 !stage->downstream_of(*(e->consumer->node))) {
1063 continue;
1064 }
1065 const auto &c_bounds = get_bounds(e->consumer->node);
1066
1067 // Get the concrete sizes of the consuming loop
1068 const auto *consumer_loop = &(c_bounds->loops(e->consumer->index, 0));
1069
1070 // Use the bounds relationship between the nodes to
1071 // map from the consumer's loop to the required region
1072 // of the producer.
1073 e->expand_footprint(consumer_loop, &(bound->region_required(0)));
1074 }
1075 }
1076
1077 // Given a required region of this producer, use the bounds
1078 // analysis to figure out what region actually gets
1079 // computed. For most funcs, these are the same. Some things,
1080 // like histograms or scans, you can only really compute all
1081 // of at once.
1082 f->required_to_computed(&(bound->region_required(0)), &(bound->region_computed(0)));
1083
1084 // Finally, figure out what loop nests will be used to compute
1085 // this region.
1086 for (int i = 0; i < (int)f->stages.size(); i++) {
1087 f->loop_nest_for_region(i, &(bound->region_computed(0)), &(bound->loops(i, 0)));
1088 }
1089
1090 const Bound &b = set_bounds(f, bound);
1091 // Validation is expensive, turn if off by default.
1092 // b->validate();
1093 return b;
1094}

1096// Recursively print a loop nest representation to stderr
1097void LoopNest::dump(string prefix, const LoopNest *parent) const {
1098 if (!is_root()) {
1099 // Non-root nodes always have parents.
1100 internal_assert(parent != nullptr);
1101
1102 aslog(0) << prefix << node->func.name();
1103 prefix += " ";
1104
1105 for (size_t i = 0; i < size.size(); i++) {
1106 aslog(0) << " " << size[i];
1107 // The vectorized loop gets a 'v' suffix
1108 if (innermost && i == (size_t)vectorized_loop_index) {
1109 aslog(0) << "v";
1110 }
1111 // Loops that have a known constant size get a
1112 // 'c'. Useful for knowing what we can unroll.
1113 if (parent->get_bounds(node)->loops(stage->index, i).constant_extent()) {
1114 aslog(0) << "c";
1115 }
1116 }
1117
1118 // Uncomment when debugging the representative loop bounds selected.
1119 /*
1120 const auto &bounds = get_bounds(node);
1121 for (size_t i = 0; i < size.size(); i++) {
1122 const auto &p = bounds->loops(stage->index, i);
1123 aslog(0) << " [" << p.first << ", " << p.second << "]";
1124 }
1125 */
1126
1127 aslog(0) << " (" << vectorized_loop_index << ", " << vector_dim << ")";
1128 }
1129
1130 if (tileable) {
1131 aslog(0) << " t";
1132 }
1133 if (innermost) {
1134 aslog(0) << " *\n";
1135 } else if (parallel) {
1136 aslog(0) << " p\n";
1137 } else {
1138 aslog(0) << "\n";
1139 }
1140 for (const auto *p : store_at) {
1141 aslog(0) << prefix << "realize: " << p->func.name() << "\n";
1142 }
1143 for (size_t i = children.size(); i > 0; i--) {
1144 children[i - 1]->dump(prefix, this);
1145 }
1146 for (auto it = inlined.begin(); it != inlined.end(); it++) {
1147 aslog(0) << prefix << "inlined: " << it.key()->func.name() << " " << it.value() << "\n";
1148 }
1149}

1151// Does this loop nest access the given Func
1152bool LoopNest::calls(const FunctionDAG::Node *f) const {
1153 for (const auto &c : children) {
1154 if (c->calls(f)) {
1155 return true;
1156 }
1157 }
1158 for (const auto *e : f->outgoing_edges) {
1159 if (e->consumer == stage) {
1160 return true;
1161 }
1162 if (inlined.contains(e->consumer->node)) {
1163 return true;
1164 }
1165 }
1166 return false;
1167}
1168
1169// What is the maximum number of inlined calls to a Func that
1170// occur within this loop. Used to prune states that would
1171// generate too much code.
1172int64_t LoopNest::max_inlined_calls() const {
1173 int64_t result = 0;
1174 for (auto it = inlined.begin(); it != inlined.end(); it++) {
1175 result = std::max(result, it.value());
1176 }
1177 for (const auto &c : children) {
1178 result = std::max(result, c->max_inlined_calls());
1179 }
1180 return result;
1181}
1182
1183// Does this loop nest access an input buffer? Used to select
1184// trail strategies when splitting loops. We don't want to read
1185// out of bounds on inputs, even if we don't intend to use the
1186// values read. It could create annoying assertion failures for
1187// the user. It's OK to read out of range of the values computed
1188// on internal Funcs though. Allocation bounds inference just pads
1189// out the bounds so that it won't fault.
1190bool LoopNest::accesses_input_buffer() const {
1191 for (const auto &c : children) {
1192 if (c->accesses_input_buffer()) {
1193 return true;
1194 }
1195 }
1196 if (is_root()) {
1197 return false;
1198 }
1199
1200 auto check = [&](const FunctionDAG::Node::Stage *s) {
1201 for (const auto *e : s->incoming_edges) {
1202 if (e->producer->is_input) {
1203 return true;
1204 }
1205 }
1206
1207 for (int t = 0; t < (int)PipelineFeatures::ScalarType::NumScalarTypes; t++) {
1208 if (s->features.op_histogram[(int)PipelineFeatures::OpType::ImageCall][t] > 0) {
1209 return true;
1210 }
1211 }
1212 return false;
1213 };
1214
1215 if (check(stage)) {
1216 return true;
1217 }
1218 for (auto it = inlined.begin(); it != inlined.end(); it++) {
1219 if (check(&(it.key()->stages[0]))) {
1220 return true;
1221 }
1222 }
1223 return false;
1224}
1225
1226// Does this loop nest contain a computation of the given Func.
1227bool LoopNest::computes(const FunctionDAG::Node *f) const {
1228 if (f == node) {
1229 return true;
1230 }
1231 if (inlined.contains(f)) {
1232 return true;
1233 }
1234 for (const auto &c : children) {
1235 if (c->computes(f)) {
1236 return true;
1237 }
1238 }
1239 return false;
1240}
1241
1242// Above here most methods query the loop nest. Below we have
1243// methods that mutate the loop nest.
1244
1245// Inline a Func into all consumers within this loop.
1246void LoopNest::inline_func(const FunctionDAG::Node *f) {
1247 // Inline it into the children
1248 for (size_t i = 0; i < children.size(); i++) {
1249 if (children[i]->calls(f)) {
1250 std::unique_ptr<LoopNest> new_child{new LoopNest};
1251 new_child->copy_from(*children[i]);
1252 new_child->inline_func(f);
1253 children[i] = new_child.release();
1254 }
1255 }
1256
1257 // Inline it here if there are any direct calls
1258 if (innermost) {
1259 int64_t calls = 0;
1260 for (const auto *e : f->outgoing_edges) {
1261 if (inlined.contains(e->consumer->node)) {
1262 calls += inlined.get(e->consumer->node) * e->calls;
1263 }
1264 if (e->consumer == stage) {
1265 calls += e->calls;
1266 }
1267 }
1268 if (calls) {
1269 inlined.insert(f, calls);
1270 }
1271 }
1272}
1273
1274// Compute a Func at this site.
1275void LoopNest::compute_here(const FunctionDAG::Node *f, bool tileable, int v) {
1276 const auto &bounds = get_bounds(f);
1277
1278 if (!may_subtile()) {
1279 // If we are restricting ourselves to the Mullapudi et al
1280 // scheduling space, then once something is computed here
1281 // we may not subtile this loop.
1282 this->tileable = false;
1283 }
1284
1285 for (int s = (int)f->stages.size() - 1; s >= 0; s--) {
1286 LoopNest *node = new LoopNest;
1287 node->node = f;
1288 node->stage = &f->stages[s];
1289 node->innermost = true;
1290 node->vectorized_loop_index = -1;
1291 node->tileable = tileable && (is_root() || may_subtile());
1292 // Set up a bound for the inside of the
1293 // loop. computed/required is still the full region, but
1294 // the loop nest will be a single representative point.
1295 auto *single_point = bounds->make_copy();
1296 size_t loop_dim = f->stages[s].loop.size();
1297 node->size.resize(loop_dim);
1298
1299 int64_t total_extent = 1;
1300 int64_t vector_size = 1;
1301 for (size_t i = 0; i < loop_dim; i++) {
1302 const auto &l = bounds->loops(s, i);
1303 // Initialize the loop nest
1304 node->size[i] = l.extent();
1305 total_extent *= node->size[i];
1306
1307 // Use the first loop iteration to represent the inner
1308 // loop. We'll shift it to a later one once we decide
1309 // on vectorization.
1310 single_point->loops(s, i) = Span(l.min(), l.min(), true);
1311
1312 internal_assert(l.max() >= l.min()) << i << " " << l.max() << " " << l.min() << "\n";
1313
1314 if (f->dimensions &&
1315 node->size[i] >= 1 &&
1316 f->stages[s].loop[i].var == f->func.args()[v]) {
1317 node->vectorized_loop_index = (int)i;
1318 vector_size = (int64_t)(node->stage->vector_size);
1319 single_point->loops(s, i).set_extent(vector_size);
1320 node->size[i] += vector_size - 1;
1321 node->size[i] /= vector_size;
1322
1323 // Shift the loops along by some multiple of the
1324 // vector size, to pick a more representative vector
1325 // than the first. We use the middle-most.
1326 int64_t shift = vector_size * (node->size[i] / 2);
1327 single_point->loops(s, i).translate(shift);
1328 } else {
1329 int64_t shift = node->size[i] / 2;
1330 single_point->loops(s, i).translate(shift);
1331 }
1332 }
1333
1334 // Leave region required blank inside the computation of a Func
1335 node->set_bounds(f, single_point);
1336 node->vector_dim = v;
1337
1338 if (node->vectorized_loop_index >= 0) {
1339 // Split off the single vector as an inner loop nest.
1340 node->innermost = false;
1341
1342 LoopNest *one_vector = new LoopNest;
1343 one_vector->node = node->node;
1344 one_vector->stage = node->stage;
1345 one_vector->tileable = false;
1346 one_vector->vectorized_loop_index = node->vectorized_loop_index;
1347 one_vector->vector_dim = v;
1348 one_vector->size.resize(loop_dim, 1);
1349 one_vector->innermost = true;
1350 auto *b = node->get_bounds(f)->make_copy();
1351 // Set the region computed inside this node to be the first vector lane
1352 b->loops(s, node->vectorized_loop_index).set_extent(1);
1353 one_vector->set_bounds(f, b);
1354 one_vector->size[node->vectorized_loop_index] = vector_size;
1355
1356 node->children.emplace_back(one_vector);
1357 }
1358 children.emplace_back(node);
1359 }
1360}
1361
1362// Parallelize this loop according to the given tiling.
1363IntrusivePtr<const LoopNest> LoopNest::parallelize_in_tiles(const MachineParams &params,
1364 const vector<int64_t> &tiling,
1365 const LoopNest *parent) const {
1366
1367 // Split this loop and move factors to the inner loop
1368 LoopNest *inner = new LoopNest, *outer = new LoopNest;
1369 inner->node = outer->node = node;
1370 inner->stage = outer->stage = stage;
1371 inner->tileable = outer->tileable = tileable && may_subtile();
1372 inner->vector_dim = outer->vector_dim = vector_dim;
1373 inner->vectorized_loop_index = outer->vectorized_loop_index = vectorized_loop_index;
1374 outer->size = size;
1375 outer->innermost = false;
1376 outer->parallel = true;
1377 outer->tileable = may_subtile();
1378
1379 // First make an inner loop representing a 1x1x1... tile
1380 inner->size.resize(size.size(), 1);
1381 inner->innermost = innermost;
1382 inner->children = children;
1383 inner->inlined = inlined;
1384 inner->bounds = bounds;
1385 inner->store_at = store_at;
1386
1387 auto *b = inner->get_bounds(node)->make_copy();
1388
1389 // Then move factors from the outer loop to the inner loop
1390 const auto &parent_bounds = parent->get_bounds(node);
1391
1392 for (size_t i = 0; i < stage->loop.size(); i++) {
1393 int l = stage->loop[i].pure_dim;
1394
1395 int64_t outer_extent;
1396 if (l >= 0) {
1397 internal_assert(l < (int)tiling.size()) << l << " " << tiling.size() << "\n";
1398 outer_extent = tiling[l];
1399 } else {
1400 // RVars are moved inwards
1401 outer_extent = 1;
1402 }
1403
1404 inner->size[i] = (outer->size[i] + outer_extent - 1) / outer_extent;
1405
1406 // Recompute the outer size given the selected inner size
1407 outer_extent = (outer->size[i] + inner->size[i] - 1) / inner->size[i];
1408
1409 outer->size[i] = outer_extent;
1410 const auto &p = parent_bounds->loops(stage->index, i);
1411 int64_t min = p.min();
1412 int64_t extent = p.extent();
1413 extent = (extent + outer_extent - 1) / outer_extent;
1414
1415 // Pick a better representative loop iteration for the
1416 // inner loops.
1417 min += (outer_extent / 2) * extent;
1418 bool compile_time_constant_bounds = p.constant_extent() || ((outer_extent > 1) && stage->loop[i].pure);
1419 b->loops(stage->index, i) = Span(min, min + extent - 1, compile_time_constant_bounds);
1420 }
1421 outer->set_bounds(node, b);
1422
1423 outer->children.emplace_back(inner);
1424 return outer;
1425}
1426
1427// Return all possible ways to compute f in tiles somewhere within
1428// this loop nest.
1429vector<IntrusivePtr<const LoopNest>> LoopNest::compute_in_tiles(const FunctionDAG::Node *f,
1430 const LoopNest *parent,
1431 const MachineParams &params,
1432 int v,
1433 bool in_realization) const {
1434 internal_assert(f);
1435
1436 vector<IntrusivePtr<const LoopNest>> result;
1437
1438 // Some pruning to not waste time on terrible states
1439 if (parent) {
1440 const auto &bounds_here = get_bounds(f);
1441 const auto &bounds_at_parent = parent->get_bounds(f);
1442
1443 // Don't descend into loops that break our ability to
1444 // vectorize if we could have vectorized one level up.
1445 const auto &p = bounds_here->region_computed(v);
1446 const auto &p_parent = bounds_at_parent->region_computed(v);
1447 int64_t e = p.extent();
1448 int64_t ep = p_parent.extent();
1449 if (ep >= f->vector_size && e < f->vector_size) {
1450 return result;
1451 }
1452
1453 // Don't descend into loops if the bounds required don't
1454 // shrink.
1455 int64_t total_here = 1, total_at_parent = 1;
1456 for (int i = 0; i < f->dimensions; i++) {
1457 const auto &range_here = bounds_here->region_computed(i);
1458 const auto &range_at_parent = bounds_at_parent->region_computed(i);
1459 total_here *= range_here.extent();
1460 total_at_parent *= range_at_parent.extent();
1461 }
1462 if (total_here >= total_at_parent) {
1463 return result;
1464 }
1465 }
1466
1467 // Figure out which child we can fuse this into
1468 int child = -1;
1469 bool called_by_multiple_children = false;
1470 for (int i = 0; i < (int)children.size(); i++) {
1471 if (children[i]->calls(f)) {
1472 if (child != -1) {
1473 called_by_multiple_children = true;
1474 }
1475 child = i;
1476 }
1477 }
1478
1479 // Place the computation directly inside this loop (provided it's not a SIMD loop)
1480 if (!innermost &&
1481 (!in_realization ||
1482 size.empty() ||
1483 vector_dim == -1 ||
1484 size[vector_dim] == 1)) {
1485
1486 std::unique_ptr<LoopNest> r{new LoopNest};
1487 r->copy_from(*this);
1488 r->compute_here(f, true, v);
1489 if (!in_realization) {
1490 r->store_at.insert(f);
1491 } else {
1492 r->tileable = false;
1493 }
1494 result.emplace_back(r.release());
1495 }
1496
1497 if (f->is_output) {
1498 // Outputs must be compute_root, so we're done.
1499 return result;
1500 }
1501
1502 if (tileable) {
1503 // The root node is not tileable, so all tileable nodes have parents.
1504 internal_assert(parent != nullptr);
1505
1506 // Generate a list of tile sizes to try
1507 auto tilings = generate_tilings(size, (int)(size.size() - 1), 2, !in_realization);
1508
1509 if (tilings.size() > 10000) {
1510 aslog(0) << "Warning: lots of tilings: " << tilings.size() << "\n";
1511 }
1512
1513 for (auto t : tilings) {
1514 if (parallel) {
1515 const auto &l = stage->loop;
1516 // More pruning. Skip root-level tilings that
1517 // would leave too many cores idle, and root-level
1518 // tilings that would force serialization of
1519 // dimensions we have decided to parallelize over
1520 // in an earlier pass.
1521 int total = 1;
1522 size_t idx = 0;
1523 for (auto s : t) {
1524 if (l[idx].pure) {
1525 total *= s;
1526 }
1527 idx++;
1528 }
1529
1530 const double tasks_per_core = (double)total / params.parallelism;
1531 const double idle_cores = std::ceil(tasks_per_core) / tasks_per_core;
1532 if (idle_cores > 1.1) {
1533 continue;
1534 }
1535 }
1536
1537 // Tile this loop and place the computation at some coarser granularity
1538 LoopNest *inner = new LoopNest, *outer = new LoopNest;
1539 inner->node = outer->node = node;
1540 inner->stage = outer->stage = stage;
1541 inner->tileable = outer->tileable = tileable && may_subtile();
1542 inner->vector_dim = outer->vector_dim = vector_dim;
1543 inner->vectorized_loop_index = outer->vectorized_loop_index = vectorized_loop_index;
1544 outer->size = size;
1545 outer->innermost = false;
1546 outer->parallel = parallel;
1547 inner->parallel = false;
1548
1549 // First make an inner loop representing a 1x1x1... tile
1550 inner->size.resize(size.size(), 1);
1551 inner->innermost = innermost;
1552 inner->children = children;
1553 inner->inlined = inlined;
1554 inner->bounds = bounds;
1555 inner->store_at = store_at;
1556
1557 {
1558 auto *b = inner->get_bounds(node)->make_copy();
1559
1560 // Then move factors from the outer loop to the inner loop
1561 const auto &parent_bounds = parent->get_bounds(node);
1562
1563 for (size_t i = 0; i < t.size(); i++) {
1564 int64_t outer_extent = t[i];
1565 inner->size[i] = (outer->size[i] + outer_extent - 1) / outer_extent;
1566 outer->size[i] = outer_extent;
1567 const auto &p = parent_bounds->loops(stage->index, i);
1568 int64_t min = p.min();
1569 int64_t original_extent = p.extent();
1570 int64_t inner_extent = (original_extent + outer_extent - 1) / outer_extent;
1571 // Pick a more representative loop iteration
1572 min += (outer_extent / 2) * inner_extent;
1573 bool compile_time_constant_extent =
1574 (p.constant_extent() || outer_extent > 1) &&
1575 (inner_extent == 1 || outer_extent == 1 || stage->index == 0);
1576 b->loops(stage->index, i) = Span(min, min + inner_extent - 1, compile_time_constant_extent);
1577 }
1578
1579 // Region_{computed/required} on outer is now
1580 // wrong, but it doesn't matter because consumers
1581 // only look at the loops in get_bounds. Still,
1582 // this is weird.
1583 outer->set_bounds(node, b);
1584 }
1585
1586 if (!in_realization) {
1587 outer->store_at.insert(f);
1588 }
1589 outer->children.emplace_back(inner);
1590
1591 // HACK
1592 // bool may_slide = false;
1593 bool may_slide = (!in_realization &&
1594 f->stages.size() == 1);
1595 if (may_slide) {
1596 // Store here, but compute further in. Currently
1597 // don't have to worry about the constraints this
1598 // places on parallelism, as we forced all the
1599 // parallelism to the outer loop.
1600 auto opts = inner->compute_in_tiles(f, outer, params, v, true);
1601 for (IntrusivePtr<const LoopNest> &n : opts) {
1602 LoopNest *store_at_outer_compute_further_in = new LoopNest;
1603 store_at_outer_compute_further_in->copy_from(*outer);
1604 store_at_outer_compute_further_in->children.pop_back();
1605 store_at_outer_compute_further_in->children.emplace_back(std::move(n));
1606 result.emplace_back(store_at_outer_compute_further_in);
1607 }
1608 }
1609
1610 // Site the computation inside the outer loop
1611 outer->compute_here(f, true, v);
1612 outer->tileable &= !in_realization;
1613 result.emplace_back(outer);
1614 }
1615 }
1616
1617 if (child >= 0 && !called_by_multiple_children && !in_realization &&
1618 (may_subtile() || is_root())) {
1619 // Push the Func further inwards in the loop nest
1620
1621 // See if it's appropriate to slide over this loop Can't
1622 // slide at the root level if we intend to parallelize it.
1623 bool may_slide = (params.parallelism == 1) || !is_root();
1624
1625 const auto &c = children[child];
1626 int num_ones = 0;
1627 for (size_t i = 0; i < c->size.size(); i++) {
1628 int64_t s = c->size[i];
1629 num_ones += (s == 1) ? 1 : 0;
1630 }
1631
1632 // Some pruning:
1633
1634 // Only slide over single-dimensional loops
1635 may_slide &= num_ones == ((int)c->size.size() - 1);
1636
1637 // Don't slide funcs with update stages
1638 may_slide &= f->stages.size() == 1;
1639
1640 // Don't slide over the vector dimension
1641 may_slide &= (c->vectorized_loop_index == -1 ||
1642 c->size[c->vectorized_loop_index] == 1);
1643
1644 for (int store_here = 0; store_here < 2; store_here++) {
1645 if (store_here && !may_slide) {
1646 // We place all our parallel loops at the root
1647 // level, so this would constrain parallelism.
1648 continue;
1649 }
1650 if (is_root() && num_ones == (int)c->size.size() && params.parallelism > 1) {
1651 // Don't fuse into serial loops, or we could never parallelize this Func.
1652 continue;
1653 }
1654 auto opts = children[child]->compute_in_tiles(f, this, params, v, store_here);
1655 for (IntrusivePtr<const LoopNest> &n : opts) {
1656 // (Only valid if one child calls f) Push the
1657 // computation into the child. Possibly leaving
1658 // the storage out here.
1659 LoopNest *r = new LoopNest;
1660 r->copy_from(*this);
1661 if (store_here) {
1662 r->store_at.insert(f);
1663 }
1664 r->children[child] = n;
1665 result.emplace_back(r);
1666 }
1667 }
1668 }
1669
1670 return result;
1671}
1672
1673// Apply the schedule represented by this loop nest to a Halide pipeline.
1674void LoopNest::apply(LoopLevel here,
1675 StageMap<std::unique_ptr<StageScheduleState>> &state_map,
1676 double num_cores,
1677 int depth,
1678 const LoopNest *parent,
1679 const LoopNest *compute_site) const {
1680 if (is_root()) {
1681 for (const auto &c : children) {
1682 Func(c->node->func).compute_root();
1683 c->apply(LoopLevel::root(), state_map, num_cores, 1, this, c.get());
1684 if (c->stage->index == 0) {
1685 auto &state = state_map.get(c->stage);
1686 state->schedule_source << "\n .compute_root()";
1687 // TODO: Omitting logic for printing store_root() assumes everything store_root is also compute root
1688 }
1689 }
1690 } else {
1691 // Non-root nodes always have parents.
1692 internal_assert(parent != nullptr);
1693
1694 if (parent->node != node) {
1695 compute_site = this;
1696 }
1697
1698 const auto &symbolic_loop = stage->loop;
1699 const auto &parent_bounds = parent->get_bounds(node);
1700 if (!state_map.contains(stage)) {
1701 StageScheduleState *state = new StageScheduleState;
1702 state->num_cores = num_cores;
1703 state->vector_dim = vector_dim;
1704 state->vectorized_loop_index = vectorized_loop_index;
1705 for (size_t i = 0; i < symbolic_loop.size(); i++) {
1706 StageScheduleState::FuncVar fv;
1707 const auto &l = symbolic_loop[i];
1708 fv.var = VarOrRVar(l.var, !l.pure);
1709 fv.orig = fv.var;
1710 fv.accessor = l.accessor;
1711 const auto &p = parent_bounds->loops(stage->index, i);
1712 fv.extent = p.extent();
1713 fv.constant_extent = p.constant_extent();
1714 fv.outermost = true;
1715 fv.parallel = l.pure && parallel;
1716 fv.exists = true;
1717 fv.pure = l.pure;
1718 fv.index = i;
1719 fv.innermost_pure_dim = (i == (size_t)vectorized_loop_index);
1720 state->vars.push_back(fv);
1721 }
1722 // Bubble the innermost pure dimension to the front of the pure dimensions
1723 for (int i = vectorized_loop_index - 1;
1724 i >= 0 && state->vars[i].pure; i--) {
1725 std::swap(state->vars[i], state->vars[i + 1]);
1726 }
1727 state_map.emplace(stage, std::unique_ptr<StageScheduleState>(state));
1728 }
1729 auto &state = *(state_map.get(stage));
1730
1731 // The getter for grabbing Func handles is reverse topological order
1732 Stage s = Func(node->func);
1733 if (stage->index > 0) {
1734 s = Func(node->func).update(stage->index - 1);
1735 }
1736
1737 if (stage->index == 0 && parent->node != node) {
1738 // Pick a memory type
1739 double bytes = node->bytes_per_point;
1740 for (int i = 0; i < node->dimensions; i++) {
1741 const auto &p = parent_bounds->region_computed(i);
1742 bytes *= p.extent();
1743 }
1744 if (bytes < 64000 && depth > 2) {
1745 // If it's probably a small allocation, and it's
1746 // made more than once, use stack-scoped
1747 // storage. Otherwise let the compiler pick heap
1748 // or stack as it likes.
1749 Func(node->func).store_in(MemoryType::Stack);
1750 state.schedule_source << "\n .store_in(MemoryType::Stack)";
1751 }
1752 }
1753
1754 // Pick a tail strategy for any splits of pure vars. RVars always use guardwithif
1755 auto pure_var_tail_strategy = TailStrategy::Auto;
1756 if (!compute_site->accesses_input_buffer() && !node->is_output) {
1757 // Roundup is lowest overhead, provided it doesn't
1758 // expand the bounds read on the input or written on
1759 // the output. However, you can only really use it on
1760 // pure stages that don't access the input anywhere in
1761 // their loop nest.
1762 pure_var_tail_strategy = TailStrategy::RoundUp;
1763 } else if (stage->index == 0) {
1764 // Pure stages that access the input use shiftinwards
1765 pure_var_tail_strategy = TailStrategy::ShiftInwards;
1766 } else {
1767 // For pure vars in update stages that access the
1768 // input, it's not safe to round up or redundantly
1769 // recompute
1770 pure_var_tail_strategy = TailStrategy::GuardWithIf;
1771 }
1772
1773 if (!size.empty()) {
1774 if (innermost) {
1775 if (vectorized_loop_index >= 0) {
1776 size_t i = 0;
1777 while (!state.vars[i].innermost_pure_dim) {
1778 i++;
1779 }
1780 auto &v = state.vars[i];
1781 internal_assert(v.innermost_pure_dim && v.exists) << v.var.name() << "\n";
1782 // Is the result of a split
1783 state.schedule_source
1784 << "\n .vectorize(" << v.var.name() << ")";
1785 s.vectorize(v.var);
1786 }
1787 } else {
1788 // Grab the innermost loop for this node
1789 const LoopNest *innermost_loop = this, *child = nullptr;
1790 while (!innermost_loop->innermost) {
1791 for (const auto &c : innermost_loop->children) {
1792 if (c->node == node) {
1793 if (!child) {
1794 child = c.get();
1795 }
1796 innermost_loop = c.get();
1797 break;
1798 }
1799 }
1800 }
1801
1802 // Do the implied splits
1803 vector<StageScheduleState::FuncVar> new_inner;
1804 for (size_t i = 0; i < symbolic_loop.size(); i++) {
1805 StageScheduleState::FuncVar v;
1806 StageScheduleState::FuncVar &parent = state.vars[i];
1807
1808 int64_t factor = (parent.extent + size[parent.index] - 1) / size[parent.index];
1809 int64_t innermost_size = innermost_loop->size[parent.index];
1810
1811 if (child && parent.innermost_pure_dim) {
1812 // Ensure the split is a multiple of the
1813 // vector size. With all these rounded
1814 // divs going on it can drift.
1815 factor = ((factor + innermost_size - 1) / innermost_size) * innermost_size;
1816 }
1817
1818 if (child && innermost_size > factor) {
1819 factor = innermost_size;
1820 }
1821
1822 if (!parent.exists || factor == 1) {
1823 v.exists = false;
1824 v.extent = 1;
1825 } else if (size[parent.index] == 1 && !(child &&
1826 child->innermost &&
1827 parent.innermost_pure_dim &&
1828 parent.var.name() == parent.orig.name())) {
1829 // Not split in this dimension
1830 v = parent;
1831 v.parallel = false;
1832 parent.exists = false;
1833 parent.extent = 1;
1834 } else {
1835 VarOrRVar inner(Var(parent.var.name() + "i"));
1836 if (parent.var.is_rvar) {
1837 inner = RVar(parent.var.name() + "i");
1838 }
1839
1840 auto tail_strategy = pure_var_tail_strategy;
1841 // If it's an RVar, or not the outermost split and we're in an update, we need a guard with if instead.
1842 if (parent.var.is_rvar || (stage->index != 0 && !parent.outermost)) {
1843 tail_strategy = TailStrategy::GuardWithIf;
1844 }
1845
1846 if (factor > parent.extent && tail_strategy == TailStrategy::ShiftInwards) {
1847 // Don't shift all the way off the image.
1848 tail_strategy = TailStrategy::GuardWithIf;
1849 }
1850
1851 s.split(parent.var, parent.var, inner, (int)factor, tail_strategy);
1852 state.schedule_source
1853 << "\n .split("
1854 << parent.var.name() << ", "
1855 << parent.var.name() << ", "
1856 << inner.name() << ", "
1857 << factor << ", "
1858 << "TailStrategy::" << tail_strategy << ")";
1859 v = parent;
1860 parent.extent = size[parent.index];
1861 v.constant_extent = (tail_strategy != TailStrategy::GuardWithIf);
1862 v.var = inner;
1863 v.accessor.clear();
1864 v.extent = factor;
1865 v.parallel = false;
1866 v.outermost = false;
1867 }
1868 new_inner.push_back(v);
1869 }
1870
1871 if (child->innermost) {
1872 // Maybe do some unrolling
1873
1874 int64_t product_of_pure_loops = 1;
1875 bool all_pure_loops_constant_size = true;
1876 for (size_t i = 0; i < symbolic_loop.size(); i++) {
1877 if (state.vars[i].pure) {
1878 product_of_pure_loops *= state.vars[i].extent;
1879 all_pure_loops_constant_size &= state.vars[i].constant_extent;
1880 }
1881 }
1882
1883 if (product_of_pure_loops <= kUnrollLimit && all_pure_loops_constant_size) {
1884 // There's a hope we can fit anything compute-at this level into registers if we fully unroll
1885 // TODO: 16 should be the number of vector registers in the architecture
1886 std::stable_sort(state.vars.begin(), state.vars.begin() + symbolic_loop.size(),
1887 [](const StageScheduleState::FuncVar &a, const StageScheduleState::FuncVar &b) {
1888 return a.pure && !b.pure;
1889 });
1890
1891 for (size_t i = 0; i < symbolic_loop.size(); i++) {
1892 if (state.vars[i].pure && state.vars[i].exists && state.vars[i].extent > 1) {
1893 s.unroll(state.vars[i].var);
1894 state.schedule_source << "\n .unroll(" << state.vars[i].var.name() << ")";
1895 }
1896 }
1897 }
1898 }
1899
1900 bool found = false;
1901 for (const auto &v : state.vars) {
1902 if (!v.exists) {
1903 continue;
1904 }
1905 here = LoopLevel(node->func, v.var);
1906 found = true;
1907 break;
1908 }
1909 if (!found) {
1910 here = LoopLevel(node->func, Var::outermost());
1911 }
1912 // internal_assert(found) << "Could not find appropriate compute_at location for children of " << node->func.name() << "\n";
1913 state.vars.insert(state.vars.begin(), new_inner.begin(), new_inner.end());
1914 }
1915 }
1916 if (innermost) {
1917 internal_assert(store_at.empty());
1918 internal_assert(children.empty());
1919 return;
1920 }
1921
1922 for (const auto *f : store_at) {
1923 Func(f->func).store_at(here);
1924 }
1925 for (auto s : size) {
1926 num_cores /= s;
1927 }
1928 here.lock();
1929 string loop_level;
1930 if (here.is_root()) {
1931 loop_level = "_root()";
1932 } else {
1933 loop_level = "_at(" + here.func() + ", " + here.var().name() + ")";
1934 }
1935 for (const auto &c : children) {
1936 if (c->node != node) {
1937 Func(c->node->func).compute_at(here);
1938 }
1939 c->apply(here, state_map, num_cores, depth + 1, this, compute_site);
1940 if (c->node != node && c->stage->index == 0) {
1941 auto &state = *(state_map.get(c->stage));
1942 state.schedule_source << "\n .compute" << loop_level;
1943 }
1944 }
1945 for (const auto *f : store_at) {
1946 bool computed_here = false;
1947 for (const auto &c : children) {
1948 if (c->node == f) {
1949 computed_here = true;
1950 break;
1951 }
1952 }
1953 if (!computed_here) {
1954 auto &state = *(state_map.get(&(f->stages[0])));
1955 state.schedule_source << "\n .store" << loop_level;
1956 }
1957 }
1958 }
1959}

1994void LoopNest::memoize_features(StageMap<ScheduleFeatures> &memoized_features, const StageMap<ScheduleFeatures> *features_to_insert) const {
1995 for (auto it = inlined.begin(); it != inlined.end(); it++) {
1996 const auto *node = it.key();
1997 const auto *stage_ptr = &(node->stages[0]);
1998 if (memoized_features.contains(stage_ptr)) {
1999 continue;
2000 }
2001
2002 internal_assert(features_to_insert->contains(stage_ptr)) << "memoize_features attempted to save a stage_ptr that doesn't exist\n";
2003 const auto &inlined_feat = features_to_insert->get(stage_ptr);
2004 memoized_features.insert(stage_ptr, inlined_feat);
2005 }
2006
2007 if (!memoized_features.contains(stage)) {
2008 internal_assert(features_to_insert->contains(stage)) << "memoize_features attempted to save this->stage but that's not in features_to_insert\n";
2009 memoized_features.insert(stage, features_to_insert->get(stage));
2010 }
2011
2012 for (const auto &c : children) {
2013 c->memoize_features(memoized_features, features_to_insert);
2014 }

2034 for (const auto &c : children) {
2035 c->recompute_inlined_features(sites, features);

2037
2038 // TODO(rootjalex): Figure out why hoisting the fetching of block / hash / cache_map breaks this loop.
2039 for (auto it = inlined.begin(); it != inlined.end(); it++) {
2040

2051 auto &intermediate = intermediate_map.get(stage);

2054 inlined_feat.inlined_calls += intermediate.inlined_calls;
2055 inlined_feat.num_scalars += intermediate.num_scalars;
2056 if (inlined_feat.innermost_pure_loop_extent > 0) {
2057 inlined_feat.innermost_pure_loop_extent =
2058 std::min(inlined_feat.innermost_pure_loop_extent,
2059 intermediate.innermost_pure_loop_extent);
2060 } else {

2067uint64_t LoopNest::compute_hash_of_producers_stored_at_root(const StageMap<Sites> &sites) const {
2068 vector<pair<int, int>> producers = collect_producers(sites);
2069
2070 // Sort them according to node id
2071 std::sort(producers.begin(), producers.end(), [](const pair<int, int> &a, const pair<int, int> &b) {
2072 return a.first < b.first;
2073 });
2074
2075 uint64_t store_root_hash = 0;
2076 for (const auto &p : producers) {
2077 hash_combine(store_root_hash, p.first);
2078 hash_combine(store_root_hash, p.second);
2079 }
2080
2081 return store_root_hash;
2082}
2083
2084vector<pair<int, int>> LoopNest::collect_producers(const StageMap<Sites> &sites) const {
2085 set<const FunctionDAG::Node::Stage *> stages;
2086 collect_stages(stages);
2087
2088 vector<const FunctionDAG::Edge *> pending;
2089
2090 for (const auto *stage : stages) {
2091 for (const auto *e : stage->incoming_edges) {
2092 pending.push_back(e);
2093 }
2094 }
2095
2096 set<const FunctionDAG::Node *> done;
2097 vector<pair<int, int>> producers;
2098
2099 // Collect all producers of the funcs within this LoopNest
2100 while (!pending.empty()) {
2101 const auto *e = pending.back();
2102 pending.pop_back();
2103 if (done.count(e->producer)) {
2104 continue;
2105 }
2106 done.insert(e->producer);
2107 const auto &site = sites.get(&(e->producer->stages[0]));
2108 if (site.store->is_root()) {
2109 int vector_dim = (e->producer->is_input ? 0 :
2110 site.produce != nullptr ? site.produce->vector_dim :
2111 -1);
2112 producers.emplace_back(e->producer->id, vector_dim);
2113 } else if (site.produce != nullptr) {
2114 // Computation must be nested inside this task or inlined into it.
2115 for (const auto &s : e->producer->stages) {
2116 for (const auto *e2 : s.incoming_edges) {
2117 pending.push_back(e2);
2118 }
2119 }
2120 }
2121 }
2122
2123 return producers;
2124}

2127 stages.insert(stage);
2128
2129 for (const auto &c : children) {
2130 c->collect_stages(stages);
2131 }

2134const LoopNest *deepest_common_ancestor(const map<const LoopNest *, pair<const LoopNest *, int>> &parents,
2135 const LoopNest *a, const LoopNest *b) {
2136 if (a->is_root()) {
2137 return a;
2138 }
2139 if (b->is_root()) {
2140 return b;
2141 }
2142 if (a == b) {
2143 return a;
2144 }
2145
2146 // Walk the deeper one up until they're at the same depth
2147 auto it_a = parents.find(a);
2148 auto it_b = parents.find(b);
2149 internal_assert(it_a != parents.end() && it_b != parents.end());
2150 while (it_a->second.second > it_b->second.second) {
2151 a = it_a->second.first;
2152 it_a = parents.find(a);
2153 }
2154 while (it_b->second.second > it_a->second.second) {
2155 b = it_b->second.first;
2156 it_b = parents.find(b);
2157 }
2158
2159 while (true) {
2160 // Walk each up one
2161 a = it_a->second.first;
2162 b = it_b->second.first;
2163 if (a == b) {
2164 return a;
2165 }
2166 it_a = parents.find(a);
2167 it_b = parents.find(b);
2168 internal_assert(it_a != parents.end() && it_b != parents.end());
2169 }
2170
2171 // unreachable
2172 return nullptr;
2173}

2175// Compute the parent and depth of every loop nest node
2176void compute_loop_nest_parents(map<const LoopNest *, pair<const LoopNest *, int>> &parents,
2177 const LoopNest *here, int depth) {
2178 for (const auto &c : here->children) {
2179 parents.emplace(c.get(), pair<const LoopNest *, int>{here, depth});
2180 compute_loop_nest_parents(parents, c.get(), depth + 1);
2181 }
2182}
